Shirsha Bose is a faculty member in the Department of Biosciences and Bioengineering at IIT Jammu. Designation: Assistant Professor. Email: shirsha.bose@iitjammu.ac.in. Education: - PhD (Loughborough University, UK; Oct 2018-Sep 2021),
- M.Tech in Polymer Science and Technology (IIT Delhi; July 2016-May 2018);
- B.Tech in Textile Technology (Government College of Engineering an. Research areas: Experimental and Computational Biomechanics, fabricating novel biomaterials, analyzing the mechanics of biological materials and bioinspired materials, and understanding the interaction of medical devices with neighbouring tissues, Blood Clot Mechanics, Biomaterials, Mechanics of calcified collagen fibre. Supervises PhD students: bsbe:Amir Ashraf, bsbe:Prangya, bsbe:Sathish.
